Chevron Lubricants Lanka PLC Key Developments

Chevron Lubricants Lanka PLC Appoints Rochana Kaul as Director/ Chairperson
Aug 2 17
Chevron Lubricants Lanka PLC announced the appointment of Ms. Rochana Kaul as Director/Chairperson of the company with effect from August 1, 2017. Rochana Kaul is general manager of Chevron Lubricants Asia/Pakistan region. She is responsible for the sales and marketing of finished lubricants and coolants in Indonesia, Malaysia, Pakistan, Philippines, Singapore, Sri Lanka, Thailand and Vietnam. Her previous assignments include General Manager, South Africa Products, along with several global & regional marketing and sales positions in lubricants across the Asia Pacific region and the Americas.


Chevron Lubricants Lanka plc Announces Resignation of Farrukh Saeed as Director/Chairman
Jul 31 17
Chevron Lubricants Lanka PLC announced resignation of Farrukh Saeed as Director/Chairman with effect from July 31, 2017, following his retirement from Chevron after 34 year of service.


Chevron Lubricants Lanka PLC Announces Unaudited Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 18 17
Chevron Lubricants Lanka PLC announced unaudited earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company's revenue was LKR 2.3 billion compared with LKR 2.8 billion a year ago. Operating profit was LKR 0.7 billion compared with LKR 1.0 billion a year ago. Profit before income tax was LKR 0.73 billion compared with LKR 1.1 billion a year ago. Profit for the period was LKR 0.53 billion or LKR 2.19 per basic share compared with LKR 0.8 billion or LKR 3.34 per basic share a year ago.

For the six months, the company's revenue was LKR 5.4 billion compared with LKR 5.9 billion a year ago. Operating profit was LKR 1.8 billion compared with LKR 2.3 billion a year ago. Profit before income tax was LKR 1.8 billion compared with LKR 2.4 billion a year ago. Profit for the period was LKR 1.35 billion or LKR 5.62 per basic share compared with LKR 1.8 billion or LKR 7.45 per basic share a year ago. Net cash generated from operating activities was LKR 0.33 billion compared with LKR 1.53 billion a year ago. Purchase of property, plant & equipment was LKR 0.013 billion compared with LKR 0.012 billion a year ago.


